**What they want from this post:** Inspiration they can genuinely connect to. Not just "here are 30 nail photos" — they want to feel understood as a Sagittarius. They want to see designs and think "yes, that's me." They also want enough practical framing to take the inspo somewhere actionable — to a salon appointment or a DIY session.

**What satisfies them:** Designs grouped by a meaningful framework (not just "here are options"), personality-resonant framing that makes them feel seen, images that cover different lengths and skin tones, and practical moments like "tell your nail tech this" or "works on short nails too."

**What frustrates them:** Generic astrology content that's identical to what they've already seen. Designs shown only on long acrylic nails when they have short natural nails. Content that leads with colour theory without showing them what it actually looks like. Repetitive purple-purple-purple without breadth.

